# Numerical Safety Rules

- Do not change formulas, convergence criteria, timestep logic, boundary condition behavior, or radiation handling without explicit justification.
- When moving numerical code, preserve calculations exactly first.
- Refactor structure before optimizing algorithms.
- If a numerical change is necessary, clearly state:
  - what changed
  - why it changed
  - expected effect
  - compatibility risk
- Prefer extracting exact logic into helper functions before redesigning it.
- Avoid combining multiple numerical behavior changes into one edit.